Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.56,0:00:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry up, Luise!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.53,0:00:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa, me and Lotte are both in opera!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.63,0:00:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not what I brought you here for. \NWe're in trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.06,0:01:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just our usual dad, not a thing is off about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.74,0:01:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch closely.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.95,0:01:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.85,0:01:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You think she might be dad's mistress?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.40,0:01:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What do I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.43,0:01:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What do I do, Luise?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.10,0:01:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise? Luise. Luise...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.71,0:01:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise... Ah, Luise?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.65,0:01:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,A dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.34,0:01:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,This is certainly bothering me a great deal
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.09,0:01:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Peperl.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.82,0:01:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.05,0:01:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me make you a tasty breakfast in return. {/in return/as a gratitude}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.92,0:01:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What could be the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.63,0:02:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise suddenly cleaning my room like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.81,0:02:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,There's more to this than meets the eye. {/I don't quite understand}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.81,0:02:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The one I knew prior to summer camp \Nis like a different person from the one that returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.65,0:02:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Before, if you peek into Luise's room...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.33,0:02:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a scene of bedlam.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.02,0:02:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Never mind cleaning, \Neven a banal tidying up seemed unthinkable.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.43,0:02:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you compare her to the current Luise...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.20,0:02:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, mind your manners.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.44,0:02:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,From today on, I will be making you \Na breakfast every morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.80,0:02:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you can come home for it, \Neven if you stayed overnight in atelier. {lit: in the times you stay/stop in atelier too, return to our home, will you? - I think she means "I want you to spend more time with me, so you'll now have reason to come home even when you sleep in atelier"}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.55,0:02:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,A mystery. {wonder; mystery; miracle; excellence}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.41,0:03:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He's deep in thought. \NCould it be because of that woman yesterday? {/from earlier}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.28,0:03:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, it must certainly be it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.14,0:03:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He is looking so restless... {/immersed in thought}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.55,0:03:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,She has not once in her life been this quiet. \NWhat might be occupying her thoughts? {/I wonder what she thinks of, that silent}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.70,0:03:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Should I ask directly?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.52,0:03:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I made up my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.72,0:03:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,- Luise. \N- Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.26,0:03:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,- What is it? \N- Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.90,0:03:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, dad, you go first.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.92,0:03:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... No, I would like to hear you out first.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.34,0:03:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Luise!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.51,0:03:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Truda stopped by to say hello. {/came to pick me up on her way}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.88,0:03:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Truda.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.30,0:03:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,School starts today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.54,0:03:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go together!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.97,0:03:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't mean to say you haven't eaten yet, do you? {/unless you haven't had your breakfast yet again}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.50,0:04:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Already finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.01,0:04:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, I'll be ready in a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.77,0:04:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm off!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.80,0:04:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We're off, Luise's dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.58,0:04:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Take care, Frauleins.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.98,0:04:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's face it, you're hiding something, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.34,0:04:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Terribly sorry, Herr Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.75,0:04:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Last night, I was feeling mighty hungry, so before I knew it, \NI helped myself to just one of your precious donuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.92,0:04:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe two.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.99,0:04:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Donuts?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.49,0:04:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Those weren't yours? {no clue if it's chigau or shiran and neither of those make sense in this and next line - "I'm mistaken/you don't know?"; would assume it was lotte who bought/baked some}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.76,0:04:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I guess it shouldn't be your concern. Yes. {again, can't fucking tell if it's kanchigau / kanji ga inatta - this sounds a lot more like kanchigau - to mistake, so it must be a mistake in prev line too}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.02,0:04:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.86,0:04:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Still struggling to make a talk with dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.04,0:04:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And it the future, it'll only get worse, I imagine. {unsure: with such thing, I can't imagine what the future looks like}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.37,0:04:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.40,0:04:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.00,0:04:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you forget the way to school?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.41,0:05:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the school Luise attends. {kayatteta is really weird way to say this}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.45,0:05:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter? \NYou look like you're seeing this school for the first time. {/with such amazement}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.85,0:05:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just that we've been away for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.82,0:05:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't wait to see my other friends again.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.37,0:05:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go now. \NWe don't want to be late.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.97,0:05:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I'll be late again.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.83,0:05:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Late!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.67,0:05:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, mind your manners! \NYou don't eat while running. {/sit when you eat}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.25,0:05:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm also running late!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.28,0:05:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Suit yourself then. \NBut I'll go ahead, now. {lit: then, mother goes first - no clue how is this related to prev line, would assume "then, if you'll be late bc you need more time to eat, I'll leave without you, unlike we usually do"}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.42,0:05:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Wait, wait! I'm coming with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.43,0:05:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you keep up with me? {guess}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.30,0:05:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.60,0:05:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going this way now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.87,0:05:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm... {no fucking clue, lit is "mother this way - I am"}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.74,0:05:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, ketchup!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.18,0:06:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, your hair roller!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.17,0:06:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Later! {dewa?}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.67,0:06:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be home by six tonight!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.35,0:06:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be waiting! {/I'm going}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.68,0:06:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, "after the poplar tree, turn right."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.78,0:06:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? This doesn't seem to be the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.35,0:06:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I followed the notes exactly, \Nbut the school is nowhere to be seen!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.39,0:06:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Found it, found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.86,0:06:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Right there!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.77,0:06:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.93,0:06:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Morning, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.55,0:06:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, did you hear? \NLotte had slapped Annie on her face yesterday!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.05,0:06:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,No way! {\i1}Our{\i0} Lotte? {\i1}Our{\i0} Annie?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.39,0:06:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Ilse!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.43,0:06:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.68,0:06:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Is everything well? {/cheerful aren't you}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.73,0:06:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't come near me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.23,0:06:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Please. And don't try to talk to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.53,0:06:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Did I offend you somehow? {/but I wasn't bullying you}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.67,0:06:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I was just trying to defend you from Annie. {/rather, I saved you from annie, I thought}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.91,0:07:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But I never asked you to slap Annie!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.87,0:07:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Now she's coming back for me later! {it's payback; tit for tat; retaliation; revenge from earlier, so my guess was right and I'm keeping the wording to follow the callback}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.38,0:07:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would she target you? \NI was the one who fought Annie, and I did it myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.35,0:07:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That's... what Annie told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.72,0:07:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Annie!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.95,0:07:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Lotte Körner, \NFrau Annie needs to have a word with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.10,0:07:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Frau Annie? A word? \NWhat's this all about?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.94,0:07:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Frau Annie had taken a grave offense\Nin your behaviour yesterday. {to take offense; to take offence; to get angry; to lose one's temper - might wanna do it the way I tled it in early eps}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.16,0:07:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,To express her protest, she won't ever again \Ncondescend to talking to Lotte personally. {/decided to not bother talking to lotte}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.87,0:07:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, from now on, she will rely on our - \NMaria and Miria's heralding services. {/will use us for messaging - technically maria and myriam are one name in german, but w/e, they aren't in the book, and I'm not sure it's mirijam, I don't hear m on the end}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.90,0:07:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Frau Annie said, until you apologize to her, \Nshe would never forgive you two! {unsure futari here refers to them two, maybe it's we two tho unlikely}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.11,0:07:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,One, two...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.33,0:07:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Is it clear?{\i0} {that's all; that is the end; the end}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.83,0:07:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What will you do, Lotte?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.55,0:07:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Annie is gravely injured this time! \NShe'll start harassing me even more!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.21,0:07:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you worry about that. \NI'll be there to protect you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.95,0:07:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.86,0:08:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that clear? When the denominator \Nis smaller than the numerator, {/therefore, ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.16,0:08:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you need to calculate how many times \Nthe nominator is more than denominator. {how many numerators you can fit into denumentaor}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.75,0:08:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte Körner?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.18,0:08:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you not feeling quite well today? {/strange}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.50,0:08:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually, I'd not expect you to fall out of line in the class. {/without being docile/quiet, you're different from usual}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.25,0:08:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what you're talking about. {/there's nothing of the kind}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.86,0:08:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, would you please tell us the answer to this problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.59,0:08:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.56,0:08:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you hear it? {/can't believe it}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.72,0:08:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte said she doesn't know it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.59,0:08:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,How odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.95,0:08:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you not been listening to my explanation at all? {properly; accurately; exactly; precisely; regularly}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.24,0:08:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Pay attention!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.86,0:08:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I will now be writing the right answers. \NEveryone, check them against your own calculations.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.11,0:08:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,She's doing it again! {/such thing}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.98,0:08:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,She thinks I'll not stand up to my promise \Njust because we're in the class!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.85,0:08:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Now this is too much!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.86,0:09:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Teacher, it's Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.83,0:09:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, what's the meaning of this? {/doing}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.46,0:09:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Shucks... She blew the whistle before I could strike. {/was noticed}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.87,0:09:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is it unsuitable? {/won't work}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.44,0:09:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you see how this article \Nis prejudiced towards one of the sides, Missis Körner?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.54,0:09:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Körner!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.97,0:09:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This article is nothing but a product \Nof extensive research on the matter!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.18,0:09:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.81,0:09:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it? We're busy now. \NYou can bring it later.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.48,0:09:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,A call for Frau Körner...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.54,0:09:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.57,0:09:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,For me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.71,0:09:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll finish this when I'm back.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.31,0:09:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn straight! {of course; certainly; naturally​}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.72,0:09:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Körner listening.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.41,0:09:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.39,0:09:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? Lotte did? In the class?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.59,0:09:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I see. \NI'll go there right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.83,0:09:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Editor, we'll have to settle our article disagreement\Nafter I return from some other place. {/we'll have plenty of exchanging opinions}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.37,0:09:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Hey, wait a minute! Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.87,0:09:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you kidding me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.47,0:09:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Which one of us is Editor-in-Chief here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.05,0:10:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems, this school is somewhat lagging behind \Nmy old school in Munich. {susumu is "to advance; to go forward" and I dunno what she means, would assume the learning program in the meaning "we're now studying more advanced subjects than they do"}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.29,0:10:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, what do I ever do about the upcoming test?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.94,0:10:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so difficult, no way anyone is going to pass! {/nobody understands}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.75,0:10:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, this is so bothersome.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.84,0:10:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Luise, can you understand that problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.01,0:10:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.88,0:10:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Margarete, do you seriously expect Luise \Nto help you with that kind of thing? {asking louise for such thing is useless} {hope it's Margarete, not in book either}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.12,0:10:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, what problem is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.62,0:10:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,This one.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.09,0:10:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.29,0:10:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,This is pretty easy. {/you solve this like that}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.43,0:10:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.59,0:10:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You bring them to the same denominator \Nand just sum up the upper part.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.16,0:10:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Great!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.38,0:10:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The same for the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.19,0:10:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, what are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.16,0:11:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.15,0:11:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me, do you also see Luise \Nexplaining the recent material to everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.12,0:11:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,This can't be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.99,0:11:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.86,0:11:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Something bad happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.16,0:11:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise is at it again! \N She hit someone and now they're crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.64,0:11:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave her alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.34,0:11:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, you're at it again?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.38,0:11:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You're wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.21,0:11:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.25,0:11:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I tripped and tore my skirt while falling!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.27,0:11:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, Luise...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.43,0:11:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Offered to mend it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.22,0:11:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.05,0:11:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,My!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.08,0:11:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.52,0:11:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, teacher? The pleasure is mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.52,0:12:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? It's about Luise again?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.57,0:12:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.70,0:12:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'll head there immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.74,0:12:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Well then...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.24,0:12:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,There we go again, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.03,0:12:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What was it this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.53,0:12:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,She fought someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.62,0:12:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.78,0:12:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, climbed the tree in the schoolyard?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.62,0:12:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.62,0:12:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing of the kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.66,0:12:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.03,0:12:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth be told, I don't know how to put it...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.86,0:12:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,She was helping the other girls to study.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.59,0:12:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.13,0:12:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,She even volunteered to water the flowerbed!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.89,0:12:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.51,0:12:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,During the class, she has also been \Nmore compliant and docile than ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.52,0:12:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,In stark contrast with before, \Nas soon as we present the problem,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.45,0:12:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,she raises her hand first in the class \Nto solve it spectacularly. {/on the opposite ... smoothly}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.62,0:13:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte bullying Annie? {/did what to annie?}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.46,0:13:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,They say, she slapped her yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.65,0:13:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,This can't be! \NShe is the most peaceful child.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.63,0:13:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Or so she has been until now...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.43,0:13:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In contrast, she's been constantly jiggling today. {(looking around) restlessly; (looking) all around; goggling​}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.80,0:13:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Made no effort whatsoever of listening to the material. {in the class}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.74,0:13:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What could have affected Lotte, \Nour exemplary student? {honor student; honours student; model student; prize pupil}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.50,0:13:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish someone would explain it to me... {unsure, maybe she means "having in mind; happening to know of; idea" - I have a hunch}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.40,0:13:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Frau Mother, did you loose your grip \Non supervising her behaviour? {/negligent supervision}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.21,0:13:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I am terribly sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.98,0:13:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if you excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.39,0:13:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. Because of me, \Nthey even called you out from work.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.93,0:13:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Never mind it. I'm certain that the person you hit \Nhad seriously deserved it, somehow.{/gave you a good reason}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.85,0:13:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.57,0:13:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Make way, make way!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.70,0:13:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Make way, you hear?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.70,0:13:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't you see I need to pass through here? {guess}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.42,0:14:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You daft dotard, don't you know who I am?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.12,0:14:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I beg your pardon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.36,0:14:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,In this town, I am quite the figure!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.29,0:14:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You find it appropriate to throw stuff \Nat a figure of such magnitude?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.20,0:14:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right! Don't you mess with my daddy! {/great/famous}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.96,0:14:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Now pick my hat up!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.76,0:14:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Pick it up, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.91,0:14:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Not so fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.97,0:14:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you treat \Nsomeone older than you this way?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.74,0:14:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? Oh-ho-ho.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.37,0:14:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Annie, isn't it that very girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.33,0:14:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The brat called Lotte that attacked you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.51,0:14:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You've a good eye, daddy. \NHere is the Lotte who had attacked me yesterday!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.69,0:14:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I could tell. \NShe has a face of a ruffian! {unsure,, maybe he means "she doesn't look like a hoodlum"}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.06,0:14:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I am Lotte's mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.86,0:14:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Your may be a figure of infinite girth,\N but you're still equal to other humans.  {/be it a celebrity or whoever }
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.96,0:14:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You will yourself pick up the hat \Nthat you dropped yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.84,0:14:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,She has a delicate face, \Nbut she likes to play strong of heart​!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.22,0:14:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.38,0:14:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You're in the school, an institution for children. {to go to and from (a place); to go back and forth between; to run between (e.g. bus, train, etc.); to ply between}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.48,0:15:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't stand you lighting a cigar here. \NBring it outside, if want it so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.26,0:15:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.26,0:15:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I like a woman who doesn't fret at the sight of me. \NNot everyone knows to speak so frankly. {/There are not many people who can say things so clearly before me}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.70,0:15:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Your intrepid kind is in decline these days. {/a strong of heart lady is good}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.82,0:15:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Please spare me your patting. {/get your hand away}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.59,0:15:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my, is he okay? {guess, "I did it"?}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.22,0:15:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Frau Körner, what a fine example \Nyou give to your daughter! {tatoe is example, but the rest - kinda dunno what she means}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.49,0:15:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You deem it appropriate for one \Nto raise a hand at others? {/infliicting violence on people is unforgivable}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.57,0:15:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,A thousand pardons.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.96,0:15:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And you, Lotte?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.24,0:15:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We're sorry! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.89,0:15:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Show some repentance! {regret; repentance; remorse; being sorry}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.15,0:15:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We repent.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.33,0:15:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,One more to the bag of unsolved mysteries! {/such a thing never happened before}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.06,0:16:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you that much concerned with her \Nsuddenly acquiring a talent for learning? {lit: it's that she became able to study, isn't it}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.11,0:16:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,This really {\i1}is{\i0} highly unusual. {/really weird thing}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.58,0:16:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't see how that is one bit unusual.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.59,0:16:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, even if your daughter's hidden talent \Nsuddenly wakes up in her, it's the most natural thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.76,0:16:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you understand? \NHer father is Herr Palfy. The acclaimed genius!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.07,0:16:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's a good explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.90,0:16:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought so, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.11,0:16:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That's relieving. \NI'm glad you could solve this for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.78,0:16:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,To you, Herr Palfy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.28,0:16:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Frau Gerlach. {from de}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.35,0:16:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no need to be that formal. {formal; strict; ceremonious; stiff}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.55,0:16:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Feel free to call me Irene.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.05,0:17:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Peperl, could you imagine it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.41,0:17:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems, that woman is none other than dad's mistress! {/mistress}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.39,0:17:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Consult with Luise? {guess}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.99,0:17:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,No way! What if mom answers the phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.60,0:17:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Still...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.18,0:17:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Five pfennig coins: 5, 10, 15, 20, and one mark. {no clue why she'd count pfennigs first and suddenly add a mark}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.15,0:17:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, 15 pfennigs in 3 notes. {lit: for 3 mae/mai, 15 ... - no clue what 3 of it is, "counter for thin, flat objects (e.g. sheets of paper, plates, coins)" would assume the paper notes, altough would likely be something they need to buy}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.08,0:17:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,With a compensation \Nfor the broken chair and the picture...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.88,0:17:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, compensation for hat, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.00,0:17:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Duly noted.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.39,0:18:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, there goes two weeks' worth of salary... {to blow off; to be blown off}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.58,0:18:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But the numerator is a month's worth! {no clue what's the joke here, not a fucking idea; maybe something about the fractions that they had in shool that louise doesn't understand?}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.70,0:18:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But at least it was fun{/refreshing}! \NI was relieved, seeing Annie's dad tumble down the stairs. {to fall down (e.g. off a chair); to slip down (e.g. one's eyeglasses); to slide down}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.56,0:18:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So did I.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.62,0:18:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, this face Annie's dad made back then!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.91,0:18:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But still, I need you to understand, Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.18,0:18:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, resorting to violence \Ndoesn't solve anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.79,0:18:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,From now on, keep your cool \N when you feel like doing it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.93,0:18:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.03,0:18:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright... Now, whatever happens, I'll be one step ahead \Nand would try to outwit Annie without violence. {/make angry}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.03,0:18:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You can count on my help with that!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.44,0:18:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Körner listening.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.54,0:18:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.85,0:18:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.32,0:18:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.45,0:19:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you like this idea...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.65,0:19:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.52,0:19:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Hung up?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.28,0:19:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That's odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.12,0:19:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello? Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.36,0:19:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Must be that they got a wrong number.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.40,0:19:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, it was you who just called, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.91,0:19:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you doing well and fine?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.04,0:19:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,How was your own first day in school?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.81,0:19:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.30,0:19:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, what's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.29,0:19:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,No, nothing. Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.79,0:19:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The school is the only good thing that happened today... {somehow}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.62,0:19:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it'll pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.37,0:19:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, I won't let you down. {/I'm doing my best too}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.83,0:19:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, where were we...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.80,0:20:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,After hearing mom's voice even for just a second, \NLotte couldn't help getting struck with feelings of longing. {/suddenly felt lonely}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.05,0:20:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,However, when the letter arrived, informing her of the commotion that Luise and mother caused in school today,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.92,0:20:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the one laughing her head off \Nwould also be none other than Lotte. {to roll about with laughter; to be convulsed with laughter; to laugh one's head off}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.93,0:21:49.49,Sign,,0,0,0,,In the next episode
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.35,0:21:53.52,Sign,,0,0,0,,We two switched places!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.52,0:21:57.25,Sign,,0,0,0,,Hey, Luise! What else could I do \Nto start getting along better with dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.25,0:22:00.50,Sign,,0,0,0,,Let me think. I know! \NDad's birthday is approaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.50,0:22:01.82,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Dad's birthday?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.82,0:22:03.52,Sign,,0,0,0,,That would be your best chance!
